                <p>I value my family very much and, even more, the moments that I spend with them. It is an important pillar in my education, in my formation and in my daily life. In spite of the defects that I have as well as all people, I try to minimize such defects with the qualities that I possess. As a young man I had the dream of being a professional basketball player and played for 13 years. I met some amazing people and I have had incredible moments all these years.</p>
                <p>All my education up to high school was done in Vila Real, city where I went to live with 7 years. I studied in a public school and gradually I learned both the subjects and to build and maintain friendly relations. I became quite communicative.</p>
                <p>During my adolescence I always dreamed of being a civil engineer but the taste for informatics was superior and I went to study in Management Informatics at Institute Polytechnic of Bragança. This period of my life has been very important, developing my knowledge and learn more new competencies, both technical and personal. I've done Erasmus program, I went to study in Poland, more precisely Poznan. All students should attend this type of programs because it gives other perspectives of life and great teachings.</p>
                <p>At this moment of my life I live and work in Lisbon, where I am a .NET programmer and consultant. I try to be a better professional every day, and always try to improve my skills and competencies. </p>
                <p>I'm not a perfect person, but I'm always trying to improve. After all, we know that maturation comes with time and experiences, and I always seek to learn from mine.</p>
